column5: Heading up to the NE end of Lac Seul in about a week, just wondering how the water level is through the rags? Also any idea how the weeds are looking up there? They seemed much more sparse that last year or two.
Fished the Bear Narrows area last week and the weeds were better than they have been the last couple years. They were holding both Pike and Walleye. Good luck, Mike Kansas
We went throught the rags with a houseboat on June 9th. Water is up 2 or 3 feet since then.Heading back up Friday. Fished shallow in June, I assume they will be deeper now.
Thank you guys for the replies, I appreciate it. Hope the weather stays like this...
